   <body>
      <p>Customer Incentive Manager performs the asynchronous validations depends on either one of the following scenarios:</p>
      <ul>
         <li>When you click the Activate button (To activate the agreement and programs). <p>OR</p>
         </li>
         <li>When you click the Validate button.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You can validate your agreement programs before you activate them to ensure that no business rules are violated. When you click Activate, your agreement is validated as well as activated. After successful activation of the agreement, the agreement status and status category changes to In Effect and Activate respectively.</p>
      <note type="note">
         <p>Validations are performed on agreements with Status as Draft, In Amendment or Activated only.</p>
         <p>Terminated or completed Agreements are excluded from validations.</p>
      </note>
      <p>For an agreement, you can validate the following:</p>
      <p>
         <ul>
            <li>
               <xref href="account_validations.xml#c259D270-BDF2-11F0-7270-09173F13E4C5">Account Validations</xref>
            </li>
            <li>
               <xref href="date_validations.xml#c259E728-BDF2-11F0-7167-09173F13E4C5">Date Validations</xref>
            </li>
            <li>
               <xref href="duplicate_product_validations.xml#c259FCE5-BDF2-11F0-2687-09173F13E4C5">Duplicate Product Validations</xref>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </p>
